# speckit Tasks: richards_sudoku

## Foundations (MVP-aligned)
- [x] Initialize project structure: `src/` package with main entry, `tests/`, basic `pyproject`/pytest config.
- [x] Implement core domain types: Cell, Board, Move, VariantMetadata, JSON schema version helper.
- [x] Build solver/validator for standard 9x9 (backtracking + constraints) and seedable generator ensuring uniqueness.
- [x] Implement model services: candidates, undo/redo (board+pencil only), timer, stats tracking.
- [x] Persistence: versioned JSON save/load with atomic write; prompt for path; round-trip tests.
- [x] PyQt6 UI shell: main window, grid widget, actions (new/load/save/import/export/hint/pencil/undo/redo), keyboard/mouse + keyboard-only navigation; light/dark (Arial, min font 6pt).
- [x] Wire basic flow: new standard game -> generate -> render; edit -> undo/redo; save/load restores timer/stats/candidates.
- [x] Tests: unit for solver/generator/persistence; pytest-qt smoke for grid render/select/undo/redo.

## SukakuExplainer (SE) Difficulty Engine

### Core Engine — COMPLETE
- [x] Design and implement `_WorkingGrid`: mutable simulation copy seeded from `cell.is_fixed` clues only; tracks `values`, `candidates`, unit/peer maps, variant name and constraints.
- [x] Implement `_build_unit_groups(size, region_layout)` → row/col/region unit lists.
- [x] Implement `_build_peer_map(size, all_units)` → cell → frozenset-of-peers mapping.
- [x] Implement shared elimination helpers: `_eliminate_from_unit`, `_reduce_cells_to`, `_elim_val_in_row_excl`, `_elim_val_in_col_excl`, `_elim_val_in_unit_excl`.
- [x] Scoring algorithm: weighted average of step weights (sum / count), capped at 8.0; contradiction returns `(8.0, "Invalid")`; no-progress unsolved returns `(8.0, "Extreme")`; already solved returns `(0.0, "Unknown")`.
- [x] Implement `score_to_label(score)` → Easy / Medium / Hard / Extreme / Unknown.
- [x] Implement `grade(board, meta) -> (float, str)` public API: build `_WorkingGrid`, run technique loop, return score and label.

### Technique Registry — COMPLETE (17 techniques)
- [x] `_LastValue` (weight 1.0): place value when one empty cell remains in a unit.
- [x] `_HiddenSingleBlock` (weight 1.2): hidden single in region units.
- [x] `_HiddenSingleLinear` (weight 1.5): hidden single in row/col units.
- [x] `_Str8tsRun` (weight 1.7): run-sequence elimination for Str8ts variant (`meta.constraints["black_cells"]`).
- [x] `_KillerCage` (weight 1.9): cage-sum elimination for Killer variant (`meta.constraints["cages"]`); permutation enumeration per cage.
- [x] `_NakedSingle` (weight 2.3): cell with exactly one candidate.
- [x] `_Pointing` (weight 2.6): locked candidates region → row/col.
- [x] `_Claiming` (weight 2.8): locked candidates row/col → region.
- [x] `_NakedPair` (weight 3.0): naked subset of size 2 across all units.
- [x] `_XWing` (weight 3.2): generalized fish degree 2 (row- and col-based).
- [x] `_HiddenPair` (weight 3.4): hidden subset of size 2 across all units.
- [x] `_NakedTriple` (weight 3.6): naked subset of size 3.
- [x] `_Swordfish` (weight 3.8): generalized fish degree 3.
- [x] `_HiddenTriple` (weight 4.0): hidden subset of size 3.
- [x] `_NakedQuad` (weight 5.0): naked subset of size 4.
- [x] `_Jellyfish` (weight 5.2): generalized fish degree 4.
- [x] `_HiddenQuad` (weight 5.4): hidden subset of size 4.

### SE Integration
- [x] Wire `grade(board, meta)` into `GameController`: call after puzzle generation (new game) and after puzzle load; store result in `_se_rating`.
- [x] Display SE score and label in PyQt6 status bar (`"SE: {label} ({score:.1f})"`); update on each new game / load event via `_refresh_difficulty_label()`.
- [x] Expose `grade()` result in save/load JSON schema (`"se_score"`, `"se_label"` fields; schema version bump to 2); restore on load without recomputing.

### SE Tests — COMPLETE
- [x] Unit test `score_to_label`: boundary values (0.0, 2.0, 4.0, 6.0, 6.1, 8.0).
- [x] Unit test `grade()` on a trivially pre-solved board → `(0.0, "Unknown")`.
- [x] Unit test `grade()` on a contradictory board (duplicate fixed clue) → `(8.0, "Invalid")`.
- [x] Unit test `grade()` on a minimal naked-single-only puzzle → score ≤ 2.0 (Easy).
- [x] Unit test each technique fires on a hand-crafted minimal fixture (one test per technique class).
- [x] Unit test Str8ts path: board with `black_cells` constraint reduces run candidates correctly.
- [x] Unit test Killer path: board with `cages` constraint eliminates invalid cage values correctly.
- [x] Regression test: grade a set of known-difficulty 9x9 puzzles and assert expected label.
- [x] Performance test: `grade()` on a 9x9 puzzle completes in < 100ms.
- [x] Performance test: Killer cage permutation on a cage of 5+ cells does not hang (cap or prune if needed).

### SE Advanced Techniques — Future
- [ ] `_XYWing` (weight ≈5.6): pivot `{X,Y}` + wings `{X,Z}/{Y,Z}`; eliminate Z from cells seeing both wings; add to `_TECHNIQUES` after `_HiddenQuad`.
- [ ] `_XYZWing` (weight ≈5.8): pivot `{X,Y,Z}` + wings `{X,Z}/{Y,Z}`; eliminate Z from cells seeing all three; add to `_TECHNIQUES` after `_XYWing`.
- [ ] `_UniqueRectangle` (weight ≈6.0–6.5): detect deadly pattern in 2×2 bi-value cells across two regions; restrict candidates to break ambiguity (types 1–4).
- [ ] `_BUG` (weight ≈6.5): bivalue universal grave — all but one unsolved cell is bivalue; force placement of the extra candidate.
- [ ] `_AlignedPairExclusion` (weight ≈6.5–7.0): pairwise constraint elimination across cells aligned in a unit.
- [ ] `_ForcingChain` (weight ≈7.0+): assumption-based chain; detect contradiction to force value or elimination.
- [ ] Calibrate weights against reference puzzle sets; adjust score thresholds if Easy/Medium/Hard/Extreme boundaries drift.

