- [x] **B1** `solver/variant_generators.py` (new file): implement `JigsawRegionGenerator(size, seed, difficulty)` — iterative cell-swap + BFS connectivity; difficulty-scaled swap count; `.generate() -> list[list[int]]`.
- [x] **B2** `solver/variant_generators.py`: implement `Str8tsMaskGenerator(size, seed, difficulty)` — point-symmetric seeded black-cell placement; canonical density values (VQ1 — spec authoritative over code): Easy 10 %, Medium 15 %, Hard 20 %, Expert 25 %; guarantee every straight segment has length ≥ 2 (R6 Q3a); `.generate() -> set[tuple[int,int]]`. `Str8tsWorker` calls this and writes result into `meta.constraints["black_cells"]` before passing `meta` to `generate_puzzle`; `generate_puzzle` only reads the mask (R8 Q3).
