- [x] **B4** `solver/generator.py`: add keyword-only params to `_fill_grid` — `meta=None`, `constraint_ok=None`, `cancel_flag=None`. Check `cancel_flag[0]` every 1 000 calls; call `constraint_ok(meta, grid, r, c, val)` if not `None`, skip `val` if it returns `False`. Jigsaw passes `None` for `constraint_ok`; Str8ts and Killer register callbacks via the variant registry.
- [x] **B5** `solver/generator.py`: add `cancel_flag=None` **and `constraint_ok=None`** to `_count_solutions`; check `cancel_flag[0]` every 1 000 calls; return `0` on cancel; pass `constraint_ok` into the backtracking loop so the uniqueness check is cage-aware for Killer (R5 Q4). Add `cancel_flag=None` and `constraint_ok=None` to `_has_unique_solution`; pass both through to `_count_solutions`. The parameter name in both `_has_unique_solution` and `_count_solutions` is `constraint_ok` throughout (no `validator` name anywhere); `validate_kakuro` is passed as `constraint_ok`; `check_unique` passes its own `constraint_ok` argument directly to `_has_unique_solution`'s `constraint_ok` parameter — no bridging rename. (R13 Q1, Option A) Also add a public `check_unique(meta: VariantMetadata, board_state: list[list[int]], constraint_ok: Callable | None = None, cancel_flag: list[bool] | None = None) -> bool` function that delegates to `_has_unique_solution`; this is the canonical entry point for complete-pipeline workers (`OneToTwentyFiveWorker`, `KenKenWorker`, `KakuroWorker`, `CodewordsWorker`) that bypass `generate_puzzle`. (R12 Q2, Option B) `_count_solutions` and `_has_unique_solution` already carry both params (confirmed in existing code); only the public `check_unique` wrapper remains. **Implementation scope (GQ-2, Option B)**: add `check_unique` now in Beta.
- [x] **B6** `solver/generator.py`: add `meta=None`, `constraint_ok=None` to `generate_solution`; pass through to `_fill_grid`. All existing positional call sites remain compatible (R1 Q1 additive approach).
- [x] **B7** `solver/generator.py`: add `meta=None`, `constraint_ok=None`, `cancel_flag=None` to `generate_puzzle`; Str8ts pre-processing; Killer skip-partition logic; raises `GenerationCancelled` on cancel.
- [x] **B8** Tests (`tests/test_solver.py` extend; new `tests/test_variant_generators.py`): `JigsawRegionGenerator` produces exactly `size` connected regions each of `size` cells; `Str8tsMaskGenerator` density in range, no segment < 2; `CagePartitioner` full coverage, no overlap, sums correct; `generate_puzzle` with `cancel_flag=[True]` raises `GenerationCancelled`; Str8ts meta produces valid consecutive straights.

