### Difficulty & Calibration

- [x] **DC1** Difficulty-dependent clue counts: `_DIFFICULTY_GIVENS = {easy: 40, medium: 32, hard: 27, expert: 23}` — same table for all variants; for Str8ts use **density-preserving scaling**: `floor(white_cell_count × _DIFFICULTY_GIVENS[difficulty] / 81)` white cells retain given values — a mask with fewer white cells produces proportionally fewer clues, preserving relative difficulty across mask densities **(VQ-D, Option B)**; Killer applies during initial digit-removal phase; no variant-specific table needed (R7 Q4).
- [x] **DC2** Difficulty-dependent Killer `is_fixed` assignment: Easy → single-cell cages `is_fixed=True`; Medium → smallest 30 % of cages all cells `is_fixed=True`; Hard/Expert → all cells `is_fixed=False`. **Implementation (GQ-4, Option C)**: `generate_puzzle()` owns this — extend the Killer early-return path (where `constraints.get("cages") is not None`) to apply difficulty-based cell population before returning `(puzzle, solution)`.
- [x] **DC3** Difficulty-dependent Str8ts black-cell digit exposure: Easy exposes given digits in **all** black cells (`is_fixed=True`); Medium exposes `floor(total_black_cells × DIFFICULTY_GIVENS["medium"] / DIFFICULTY_GIVENS["easy"])` = `floor(total_black_cells × 0.8)` black cells — 80 % exposure (same fraction as the difficulty-scaled clue-count formula; GQ8); Hard/Expert black cells carry no given digits. **Implementation (GQ-5, Option B)**: `generate_puzzle()` owns this — inside the Str8ts pre-processing block, use a seeded-random shuffle of the black-cell list to select the exposure subset, then populate `meta.constraints["black_givens"]` as `[[r, c, v], …]` from the solution; `Str8tsMaskGenerator` returns positions only, solution digits come from `generate_solution`.
- [x] **DC4** Calibrate SE grader weights against reference puzzle sets; adjust thresholds if Easy/Medium/Hard/Extreme boundaries drift for tested variants.

